<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06241103 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06241103 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  In Concord, N.H., a judge denied three of four motions in instructor PamelaSmart's attempt to get a new trial on charges that she coaxed her teen-agelover and his friends into killing her husband. The judge did not rule on afourth motion that claims media coverage tainted the jury. Smart's attorneysaid that motion is the most important. Smart, 24, was convicted in March ofcoercing her teen-age lover, William Flynn, and his two friends into killingher husband, Gregory Smart, 24.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  DEATH-PLOT FIGURE DENIED NEW TRIAL  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  National News in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910828  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  4A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  90  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday, August 28, 199100241103,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>